{"type":"finding","iteration":13,"id":"S2-05C-reducer-exhausted-index","dimension":"D1","focus":"S2-05","summary":"Kasper preserves rejected patterns across external state merges by set-unioning on-disk rejections into memory; our reducer currently builds exhausted approaches from literal deadEnds/ruledOut text and can grow duplicate blocked categories when wording shifts.","sourceRefs":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:994",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:995",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:996"],"targetFile":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs","supportFiles":[".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md"],"portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win","whyItHelps":"Lets exhausted approaches derive from a capped semantic rejected-idea index, making negative knowledge stable across resume, recovery, and wording drift."}
{"type":"finding","iteration":13,"id":"S2-05D-explicit-undo-reset-semantics","dimension":"D1","focus":"S2-05","summary":"Kasper rejection persistence is not irreversible: removeRejectedPattern deletes one pattern and reset clears rejected_patterns, so the durable suppression contract is until explicit undo/reset rather than forever.","sourceRefs":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:514",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:515",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:518",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:571",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:575"],"targetFile":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","supportFiles":[".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md"],"portDifficulty":"easy","tag":"quick-win","whyItHelps":"Gives operators an intentional way to revive a rejected direction while preventing ordinary stuck recovery from clearing the suppression cache."}
{"type":"observation","iteration":13,"id":"observation:S2-05:manual-rejection-ux-removed-caveat","summary":"The current kasper tree still contains the durable rejection state and filters, but older integration tests note that the explicit kasper_reject feedback-loop tools were removed; treat this finding as a state/filter protocol import, not proof of a currently complete manual rejection UX.","reference":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/tests/integration.test.ts:526",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:502",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/evaluate.ts:1659"],"target":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md"}
